This paper deals with the problem of scheduling data processing workflows, which is a common topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of machine learning to optimize the scheduling decisions suggests that this paper could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed workflow model in a middleware framework, which could be considered software engineering (cs.SE) or computer engineering (cs.CE).
